6. Fixes (Grouped by Area)
Controller (slurmctld)
Fixed interactive jobs erroneously killed by InactivityLimit under controller congestion.
Fixed possible crash from pointer-comparison mismatches under heavy load.
Fixed crashes: HetJob component failing to start; removing all of a pending job's licenses; race condition during startup (I/O processed before conn plugin init); race in x11 forwarding (double free); segfault scheduling on GRES reservations after restart.
Fixed hangs/deadlocks: during reconfigure/shutdown from slow client I/O; race condition during shutdown reading a connection.
Fixed unresponsive nodes not being marked DOWN on clusters with frequent reconfigures.
Fixed reservation bugs: overlap checks missing conflicts across DST transitions; incorrect error messages in overlap sanity checks; deadlock replacing nodes in reservations; retained-node bug after nodes move out of a reservation's partition; jobs not held when a requested reservation is purged; reservation updates not persisting to DB.
Fixed DefMemPerCPU formatting; IPv6 control-host bracketing in scontrol show federation.
Fixed node-reboot handling with older slurmd; background thread no longer waits on purge-files thread while holding job/node write locks.
Various performance/lock-contention fixes (dbd agent packing, avoiding reverse DNS lookups unless DebugFlags=conmgr set, node-write-lock removal for several read-only RPCs).
Accounting (slurmdbd / accounting_storage)
Fixed performance regression from lock contention packing dbd-agent messages.
Fixed state-replay message leak on version mismatch.
Fixed crash/deadlock races during shutdown (persistent connections, federation active, service-connection teardown).
Fixed sacctmgr load parsing for files with typed TRES; runtime-added assoc/wckey UID NO_VAL under use_client_ids.
Improved hourly rollup and archive/purge performance on large/active clusters.
Fixed ~37s extra delay in slurmdbd reconnection retries on NTP-synced systems.
Compute Node / Job Execution (slurmd, slurmstepd)
Fixed HetJob step-launch crash between 26.05 slurmd and older (≤24.11) srun.
Fixed incompatibility between 26.05 slurmd and 25.05+ slurmstepd when a 24.11 sattach is used (would hang).
Fixed memory leaks in cgroup plugin init and jobacctinfo aggregation crash under enable_stepmgr + jobacct_gather/none.
Fixed jobs stuck in COMPLETING with PrologFlags=RunInJob.
Fixed epilog running multiple times on TERMINATE_JOB retries.
Scheduling / stepmgr / Topology
Fixed torus3d placement overlap detection and node-count overflow guard; added adaptive Morton encoding for large torus dimensions.
Fixed slow scheduling for multi-segment jobs under topology/block with undersized blocks.
Fixed stepmgr crashes/leaks: async step launch crash across mismatched srun/slurmd releases; memory leak in stepmgr stepd; sbcast with auth/slurm issues.
Reject/validate fixes: reject sbatch --external combined with --wrap; reject jobs where num_tasks < min_nodes; validate --segment and arbitrary task distribution against incompatible options (topology/block, --spread-job, CR_LLN, etc.).
REST API (slurmrestd)
Fixed pipelined HTTP/1.1 keep-alive request handling; memory leak on early connection termination.
Fixed memory leak from empty node_list in reservation POST bodies.
Fixed 200-vs-404 behavior querying nonexistent partitions.
Numerous v0.0.45 field additions/renames (see Breaking Changes and New Features).
CLI Tools
sh5util: fixed HDF5 "Malformed file" error on -I extraction, memory leaks, exit code for -h/-V.
sacctmgr: fixed silently-ignored trailing characters in numeric options, default-account removal bug with multiple defaults, quiet/verbose mutual exclusivity.
scontrol: fixed listpids output when a step terminates mid-query; array-job-id formatting in error messages.
srun: reject --async outside an existing allocation; fixed minor memory leaks in job description handling; removed old broken exit-code-108 retry logic for Open MPI.
GPU (gpu/nvml)
Fixed --gpu-freq to set actual memory/GPU clocks (not deprecated "applications clocks") on CUDA 11.3+, preventing build errors on CUDA 13.0+.
Fixed clock-frequency reset across multiple GPUs at job completion under cgroup device constraints.
Fixed --gpu-freq application without an explicit memory clock frequency.
Networking / Switch (switch/hpe_slingshot)
Fixed memory leak on fabric-manager 404 responses to job-lookup GETs.
Fixed non-stepmgr extern steps incorrectly trying to delete jobs from the fabric manager on completion.
Packaging / Build
Fixed gcc-16 and FreeBSD build issues; _unitdir fallback typo in slurm.spec; rpmbuild --with selinux.
Fixed shtml2html.py warning under Python 3.14+.
